1) cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the application of wavelet transform in compressed sensing-based signal reconstruction, which falls under the purview of information theory. 
2) cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a learning-based approach for wavelet transform, which can be considered as a machine learning problem. 
3) cs.SP (Signal Processing): The paper deals with signal processing techniques, specifically wavelet transform. 
4) cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Wavelet transform is widely used in image processing and computer vision applications, and the proposed method can be applied in these areas. 
5) cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the mathematical framework of wavelet transform and its application in signal processing, which falls under the purview of numerical analysis.
